Hey, back it up!
 What do you... Wait.
 Just back it up! Hold on!

1245
01:11:03,389 --> 01:11:08,916
Lady, if you want
 to get arrested, tell us now,
 and save us a lot of time.

1246
01:11:09,047 --> 01:11:12,746
Please, Officer.
I must see Stone Adams.

1247
01:11:12,877 --> 01:11:14,661
It's crucial.

1248
01:11:14,792 --> 01:11:17,229
It's crucial that
you get yourself a pass
or you stay over there.

1249
01:11:21,146 --> 01:11:23,017
-How did it go?
 -It didn't.

1250
01:11:23,148 --> 01:11:24,584
Those cops were all over me.

1251
01:11:26,282 --> 01:11:28,414
They're never
 gonna let me in there.
 I've gotta figure...

1252
01:11:39,077 --> 01:11:41,079
All right, extras!
 We're ready to shoot one.

1253
01:11:41,209 --> 01:11:44,517
I need everybody inside.
 Come on, come on, move it!

1254
01:11:44,648 --> 01:11:47,346
You again. What's the matter,
 you don't understand English?

1255
01:11:47,477 --> 01:11:51,350
That's just it.
 I taught Stone Adams English.

1256
01:11:51,481 --> 01:11:53,134
I thought it was drama.

1257
01:11:53,265 --> 01:11:56,050
No, actually,
 it was drama.

1258
01:11:56,964 --> 01:11:58,183
And English.

1259
01:12:00,577 --> 01:12:01,795
[INDISTINCT]

1260
01:12:02,927 --> 01:12:05,495
Everybody, settle down.
 Are you doing okay?

1261
01:12:05,625 --> 01:12:07,497
So I whack the gun here,

1262
01:12:07,627 --> 01:12:09,760
and then he hits me
 with the chair there?

1263
01:12:09,890 --> 01:12:13,111
Right, Stone.
 It's a breakaway. Oh!

1264
01:12:14,373 --> 01:12:16,288
-Props!
 -MAN: I'm on it.

1265
01:12:17,768 --> 01:12:19,378
There we go...

1266
01:12:19,509 --> 01:12:22,250
-MAN: New chair quick.
 -Thank you.
 You, you sit over here...

1267
01:12:22,381 --> 01:12:24,818
When the fight starts,
 you move over there. Okay?

1268
01:12:24,949 --> 01:12:27,995
All right! Lock it up!
 Here we go! Hit it.

1269
01:12:28,561 --> 01:12:29,780
All right, people...

1270
01:12:31,477 --> 01:12:32,435
Gum.

1271
01:12:33,218 --> 01:12:34,219
Psst!

1272
01:12:35,307 --> 01:12:37,353
MAN:  <i>Gang Land, 14-D,</i>
 take one.

1273
01:12:38,441 --> 01:12:39,442
Psst...

1274
01:12:40,443 --> 01:12:43,402
Psst... Psst... Stone...

1275
01:12:45,578 --> 01:12:49,321
DIRECTOR: Quiet on the set.
 Let's go. Settle down, people.

1276
01:12:49,452 --> 01:12:51,976
I think you dropped
 a dime on me to the cops.

1277
01:12:52,106 --> 01:12:53,151
Why would I do that?

1278
01:12:54,457 --> 01:12:56,807
Because you figure
 you can run things yourself.

1279
01:12:56,937 --> 01:12:59,157
Well, I'm not
 the running things
 kind of guy.

1280
01:13:00,158 --> 01:13:02,552
I say, I think you are.

1281
01:13:03,814 --> 01:13:04,815
[GUN CLICKING]

1282
01:13:04,945 --> 01:13:06,817
You're not going
 to kill me here.

1283
01:13:06,947 --> 01:13:08,340
You got a better
place in mind?

1284
01:13:08,862 --> 01:13:09,907
[CHUCKLES]

1285
01:13:16,435 --> 01:13:17,393
[GLASS SHATTERING]

1286
01:13:17,523 --> 01:13:19,177
WOMAN: Cut! Stone?

1287
01:13:19,307 --> 01:13:23,224
Stone? You okay? You okay?

1288
01:13:23,355 --> 01:13:25,226
What's going on?
This was supposed to be
a breakaway.

1289
01:13:25,357 --> 01:13:27,925
I swear! I got the chair
 from the extra!

1290
01:13:28,055 --> 01:13:29,230
WOMAN: Stone, can you hear me?

1291
01:13:40,633 --> 01:13:43,244
What can cause
 holes like that?

1292
01:13:43,375 --> 01:13:45,899
Mice the size of Chihuahuas?

1293
01:13:46,030 --> 01:13:47,945
-So you see what I mean.
 -[RUMBLING]

1294
01:13:49,947 --> 01:13:51,905
Uh, Mrs. Caldwell...

1295
01:13:52,036 --> 01:13:53,211
Not now, Normann.

1296
01:13:53,341 --> 01:13:54,386
But...

1297
01:13:59,522 --> 01:14:00,697
[SCREAMING]

1298
01:14:05,092 --> 01:14:08,052
It's gonna blow!

1299
01:14:09,749 --> 01:14:12,622
Can there be any doubt
 what needs to be done here?

1300
01:14:15,712 --> 01:14:17,583
Normann, may I speak with you?

1301
01:14:21,805 --> 01:14:25,069
-[GASPS] What happened?
-Don't ask.

1302
01:14:25,896 --> 01:14:27,593
Just a second, Officer.

1303
01:14:27,724 --> 01:14:30,727
If you arrest her,
 you'll have to arrest me.

1304
01:14:30,857 --> 01:14:32,380
What... There's two of you?

1305
01:14:33,599 --> 01:14:35,253
Have it your way, lady.

1306
01:14:35,383 --> 01:14:36,907
Okay. Let's go.

1307
01:14:42,956 --> 01:14:44,392
PATTY: Thanks for
bailing us out.

1308
01:14:44,523 --> 01:14:46,177
RICHARD: I spoke
 to the production company.

1309
01:14:46,307 --> 01:14:48,135
They said they're gonna
 drop the charges.

1310
01:14:48,266 --> 01:14:49,267
PATTY: And Stone's okay?

1311
01:14:49,397 --> 01:14:50,616
Apparently.

1312
01:14:50,747 --> 01:14:52,923
He said it only hurts
when he thinks of you.

1313
01:14:53,532 --> 01:14:55,447
He hates me.

1314
01:14:55,578 --> 01:14:58,668
Of course, he'll have to get
 in line behind all these
 people after tonight.

1315
01:14:59,799 --> 01:15:01,453
What am I going to say?

1316
01:15:01,584 --> 01:15:03,281
Why don't you try the truth?

1317
01:15:03,411 --> 01:15:04,456
[CHUCKLES]

1318
01:15:05,631 --> 01:15:07,154
I don't see
the rest of the family.

1319
01:15:07,285 --> 01:15:08,765
They should be here
 any minute.

1320
01:15:08,895 --> 01:15:11,158
Good luck.

1321
01:15:11,289 --> 01:15:13,334
You were supposed to hire
 a limo for tonight.

1322
01:15:13,465 --> 01:15:16,555
I'm sorry, Mrs. C, but there
 still seems to be a problem
 with your credit cards.

1323
01:15:16,686 --> 01:15:19,036
No doubt, thanks to Patty
 and that family of hers.

1324
01:15:19,166 --> 01:15:22,430
I can hardly wait
to see her face when
she discovers the news.

1325
01:15:22,561 --> 01:15:24,389
[LAUGHING]

1326
01:15:24,520 --> 01:15:27,218
Everyone who bought a ticket
 actually showed up.

1327
01:15:27,348 --> 01:15:29,960
And some of them brought
 those big checks
 you were looking for.

1328
01:15:30,613 --> 01:15:32,832
Ah. Well, it's a shame

1329
01:15:32,963 --> 01:15:35,139
I couldn't find
 any entertainment for them.

1330
01:15:36,444 --> 01:15:39,447
Oh. Oh, that is bad news.

1331
01:15:39,578 --> 01:15:43,321
Uh, would you like to make
 the announcement yourself?

1332
01:15:59,685 --> 01:16:00,991
Excuse me...

1333
01:16:02,340 --> 01:16:04,734
Uh, hi...

1334
01:16:06,692 --> 01:16:11,001
My name is Patty Lane,
 and, um...

1335
01:16:13,481 --> 01:16:16,397
A funny thing happened
on the way to
the celebrity concert.

1336
01:16:16,528 --> 01:16:18,399
MAN:  <i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i><i>
please welcome</i>

1337
01:16:18,530 --> 01:16:21,359
<i>award-winning</i>
<i>performing artists</i>
<i>and BHHS alumni,</i>

1338
01:16:21,489 --> 01:16:22,969
<i>"The Bomb."</i>

1339
01:16:23,100 --> 01:16:25,624
<i> ♪ After all these years, <i>
 after all that's come and gone</i></i>

1340
01:16:25,755 --> 01:16:28,105
<i>♪ We're back, we're back,</i>

1341
01:16:28,235 --> 01:16:31,412
<i>♪ After all is said and done</i>
<i>we're back ♪</i>

1342
01:16:31,543 --> 01:16:32,718
Surprise.

1343
01:16:32,849 --> 01:16:35,068
Stone! Oh!

1344
01:16:35,199 --> 01:16:36,896
Oh, watch it, watch it!
Injury, injury, injury.

1345
01:16:37,027 --> 01:16:38,202
Oh, I'm sorry,
 I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

1346
01:16:39,595 --> 01:16:41,292
I can't believe you're here.

1347
01:16:41,422 --> 01:16:43,381
Well, believe it.
 It's show time. Follow me.

1348
01:16:43,947 --> 01:16:45,296
[APPLAUSE]

1349
01:16:47,559 --> 01:16:50,388
Ladies and gentlemen,
 may I have your attention,
 please?

1350
01:16:50,518 --> 01:16:53,130
On behalf of
 the New York city schools,

1351
01:16:53,260 --> 01:16:56,046
and all of your
 very grateful former students,

1352
01:16:56,176 --> 01:16:59,789
I proudly present to you
 the Clarissa Anthony award.

1353
01:16:59,919 --> 01:17:01,399
Congratulations.

1354
01:17:01,529 --> 01:17:03,488
[ALL CHEERING]

1355
01:17:03,619 --> 01:17:06,622
The Clarissa Anthony award
 is a lifetime achievement
 award for teaching.

1356
01:17:11,191 --> 01:17:12,497
[WHISTLING]

1357
01:17:20,940 --> 01:17:27,294
Folks, teaching is
 one of the most important
 professions there is

1358
01:17:27,425 --> 01:17:30,254
because teachers
 are the ones who, who

1359
01:17:30,384 --> 01:17:32,691
mold our future for all of us.

1360
01:17:33,692 --> 01:17:36,739
Now we owe a huge debt
to Patty Lane,

1361
01:17:36,869 --> 01:17:38,654
and every other
 teacher out there,

1362
01:17:38,784 --> 01:17:42,788
who continually
 puts the students
 in the starting position.

1363
01:17:44,485 --> 01:17:47,619
It is your passion,
 your inspiration,

1364
01:17:49,316 --> 01:17:50,709
and your dedication

1365
01:17:52,885 --> 01:17:54,234
that are all too rare.

1366
01:17:55,496 --> 01:17:56,759
Thank you, Miss Lane.

1367
01:17:57,934 --> 01:17:59,196
Thank you for being you.

1368
01:18:00,501 --> 01:18:01,764
[ALL CHEERING]

1369
01:18:21,305 --> 01:18:23,089
-I'm speechless.
-[ALL LAUGHING]

1370
01:18:23,220 --> 01:18:24,308
Um...

1371
01:18:25,048 --> 01:18:26,614
Except to say that this is

1372
01:18:27,615 --> 01:18:29,313
the best night of my life.

1373
01:18:31,228 --> 01:18:34,710
And those of you
 who kept the secret,

1374
01:18:35,841 --> 01:18:37,190
I know where you live.

1375
01:18:37,713 --> 01:18:39,366
[ALL LAUGHING]

1376
01:18:39,497 --> 01:18:41,542
I wouldn't take that
 threat too lightly, folks.
 I wouldn't.

1377
01:18:41,673 --> 01:18:44,110
All right, what do you say
 we rock this joint, huh?

1378
01:18:44,241 --> 01:18:46,286
One, two,
a-one-two-three-four...

1379
01:18:46,417 --> 01:18:47,984
[LIVELY MUSIC PLAYING]

1380
01:18:57,341 --> 01:18:58,603
Let's see this thing.

1381
01:18:59,604 --> 01:19:01,519
Ah, where is Cathy?

1382
01:19:01,649 --> 01:19:03,260
Well, she had to take care of
 some important business.

1383
01:19:03,390 --> 01:19:05,044
She'll be here, though.

1384
01:19:05,175 --> 01:19:09,135
Hey, gorgeous.
 Are you busy, later?

1385
01:19:11,659 --> 01:19:12,878
Richard...

1386
01:19:13,792 --> 01:19:16,839
Are you trying to ask me out?

1387
01:19:16,969 --> 01:19:21,408
Actually, I'm trying to
ask you to consider
starting over.

1388
01:19:21,539 --> 01:19:24,194
Unless you feel
 it's a bad idea...

1389
01:19:27,850 --> 01:19:30,113
I think it's the best idea
 I ever heard.

1390
01:19:36,597 --> 01:19:40,776
Uh, mom, I'd like to read
 from my column that'll appear

1391
01:19:40,906 --> 01:19:43,126
in tonight's edition
 of the  <i>New York Sun.</i>

1392
01:19:45,955 --> 01:19:49,045
"Patty lane is a teacher
 in Brooklyn who taught
 her students

1393
01:19:49,175 --> 01:19:50,786
"to believe in themselves.

1394
01:19:50,916 --> 01:19:54,267
"Sure, she taught lessons that
 were required by the state,

1395
01:19:54,398 --> 01:19:58,010
"but she also taught
 what was required
 by the heart.

1396
01:19:58,141 --> 01:20:01,405
"She said nothing
 is impossible
 if you want it bad enough.

1397
01:20:02,449 --> 01:20:04,103
"And so, they listened,

1398
01:20:04,234 --> 01:20:05,888
"and they went out
into the world.

1399
01:20:07,324 --> 01:20:10,283
"Thousands of
 success stories validate her.

1400
01:20:11,067 --> 01:20:12,764
"And today,

1401
01:20:12,895 --> 01:20:16,507
"she saved the very school
 where she taught them
 because...

1402
01:20:18,552 --> 01:20:20,337
"Because she wanted it
 badly enough.

1403
01:20:21,599 --> 01:20:24,558
"That teacher is my mom.

1404
01:20:25,690 --> 01:20:28,736
"Thank you for teaching me
 what's important.

1405
01:20:28,867 --> 01:20:31,914
"I've never been more proud
to be your son."

1406
01:20:32,044 --> 01:20:33,350
[ALL APPLAUDING]

1407
01:20:38,790 --> 01:20:43,012
I'm moved. I really am.
 It's very touching.

1408
01:20:43,142 --> 01:20:47,843
Almost as touching
 as the fact that we
 matched the state funds.

1409
01:20:47,973 --> 01:20:51,281
Oh, but I'm afraid we're
 not talking repairs anymore.

1410
01:20:51,411 --> 01:20:53,674
I won't bore you
 with the details,

1411
01:20:53,805 --> 01:20:56,155
but I'm afraid the school
 must be torn down.

1412
01:20:56,286 --> 01:20:58,157
You'll notice
the word "demolition".

1413
01:20:58,288 --> 01:20:59,942
And the official city seal.

1414
01:21:02,031 --> 01:21:03,554
Sue Ellen,
 if I wasn't a lady...

1415
01:21:03,684 --> 01:21:04,947
GALLIANO: Hold on, there!

1416
01:21:07,427 --> 01:21:08,559
It's Mayor Galliano!

1417
01:21:10,256 --> 01:21:11,823
Hello, Patty.

1418
01:21:11,954 --> 01:21:15,392
Mr. Mayor. You know my name?

1419
01:21:15,522 --> 01:21:17,916
You're a difficult woman
 to ignore.

1420
01:21:18,047 --> 01:21:20,484
All those faxes
 and phone calls
 tying up my staff.

1421
01:21:21,659 --> 01:21:23,574
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to...

1422
01:21:23,704 --> 01:21:26,229
Look, a second inspection

1423
01:21:26,359 --> 01:21:29,797
disputed the original
 findings at BHHS.

1424
01:21:29,928 --> 01:21:33,062
So I discussed the problem
 with the board of education,

1425
01:21:33,192 --> 01:21:35,455
and convinced them
 to appropriate the funds

1426
01:21:35,586 --> 01:21:38,632
to completely renovate
Brooklyn Heights High,

1427
01:21:38,763 --> 01:21:41,722
and place it
 on the historic register.

1428
01:21:41,853 --> 01:21:46,031
So you can ignore
 that demolition order.
 It's been rescinded.

1429
01:21:46,162 --> 01:21:47,380
[LAUGHING]

1430
01:21:47,859 --> 01:21:49,774
Oh!

1431
01:21:49,905 --> 01:21:53,734
Oh, Mr. Mayor,
 I don't know how to thank you!

1432
01:21:53,865 --> 01:21:55,693
I should be
 thanking you, Patty.

1433
01:21:57,042 --> 01:22:01,264
One more thing.
 Who is Liam MacAllister?

1434
01:22:01,742 --> 01:22:03,005
LIAM: Oh, no...

1435
01:22:05,442 --> 01:22:06,530
-Uh-oh.
 -Liam...

1436
01:22:08,793 --> 01:22:12,492
I want you to
 come down to City Hall,
 do your impression of me.

1437
01:22:12,623 --> 01:22:14,581
We could use a few more
 laughs down there.

1438
01:22:14,712 --> 01:22:15,931
[ALL LAUGHING]

1439
01:22:16,844 --> 01:22:18,411
Have a nice day.

1440
01:22:18,542 --> 01:22:22,198
Patty, have a nice day.
 Sir, have a nice day.

1441
01:22:22,328 --> 01:22:23,939
Have a nice day, everybody.

1442
01:22:24,069 --> 01:22:25,288
But, Mr. Mayor...

1443
01:22:25,418 --> 01:22:26,724
Do you see him?

1444
01:22:28,247 --> 01:22:31,424
Ah, Mr. Mayor, I think
 you seem to have forgotten

1445
01:22:31,555 --> 01:22:34,384
my recent contribution
 to your re-election campaign.

1446
01:22:34,514 --> 01:22:36,081
As a matter of fact, I didn't.

1447
01:22:38,257 --> 01:22:40,564
I decided I won't be
 needing your support.

1448
01:22:40,694 --> 01:22:42,261
Thanks to Mrs. MacAllister

1449
01:22:42,392 --> 01:22:43,959
and her friends
 at the commerce department,

1450
01:22:44,089 --> 01:22:47,005
I've become aware
 of your business dealings.

1451
01:22:47,136 --> 01:22:51,662
It seems you've been signing
 tenants and taking their money

1452
01:22:51,792 --> 01:22:54,186
for your mall even though
 you don't own the building.

1453
01:22:54,317 --> 01:22:56,928
The district attorney
 is very interested
 in talking to you

1454
01:22:57,059 --> 01:22:59,017
about real estate fraud.

1455
01:22:59,148 --> 01:23:03,108
There's also the matter
 of bribing and misleading
 a city official.

1456
01:23:03,239 --> 01:23:05,502
Hire a good lawyer, Sue Ellen.
 You'll need one.

1457
01:23:06,633 --> 01:23:08,461
-You must be Normann.
 -Me?

1458
01:23:08,592 --> 01:23:13,640
I hope she pays you well,
 because Attica prison
 is holding a spot for you.

1459
01:23:13,771 --> 01:23:15,120
Have a nice day.

1460
01:23:16,469 --> 01:23:19,733
Mrs. MacAllister, I want
 to thank you for everything.

1461
01:23:21,039 --> 01:23:23,041
-Thank you.
 -Gentlemen, carry on!
 Pick a table.

1462
01:23:24,956 --> 01:23:26,436
[TANGO MUSIC PLAYING]

1463
01:23:30,962 --> 01:23:32,833
-This is all your fault.
 -My fault?

1464
01:23:32,964 --> 01:23:36,098
I knew I should have
hired someone with more
than three brain cells.

1465
01:23:39,275 --> 01:23:40,276
NORMANN: Mrs. C...

1466
01:23:41,973 --> 01:23:43,453
[HYSTERICAL LAUGHTER]

1467
01:23:47,892 --> 01:23:49,067
[ALL LAUGHING]

1468
01:23:57,728 --> 01:23:59,730
Have a nice day, Sue Ellen.

1469
01:24:19,967 --> 01:24:21,317
[INDISTINCT TALKING]

1470
01:24:29,194 --> 01:24:30,891
No commitments.

1471
01:24:31,022 --> 01:24:32,589
It's over when the song ends.

1472
01:24:34,286 --> 01:24:37,768
Why don't we see what happens
 when the song ends.

1473
01:24:38,682 --> 01:24:40,336
I think I like
 the sound of that.

1474
01:24:40,466 --> 01:24:42,077
[CHUCKLES]

1475
01:24:42,207 --> 01:24:45,863
Maybe Liam and Cathy
 could move into the house.

1476
01:24:45,993 --> 01:24:47,299
There's plenty of room.

1477
01:24:47,430 --> 01:24:49,388
It is pretty big just for you.

1478
01:24:49,519 --> 01:24:52,435
Well, I wasn't thinking of it
 just for me, you know.

1479
01:24:52,565 --> 01:24:53,740
I do know.

1480
01:24:55,742 --> 01:24:58,528
Oh, wouldn't it be great
 having Cath here?

1481
01:24:58,658 --> 01:25:01,400
We could raise thousands
 of dollars for the school,

1482
01:25:01,531 --> 01:25:03,707
